        Please note the rows being grouped must be in the current window, if the rows are already flushed then groupRow has no effect.

        Correct code: 
        
       Workbook wb = new SXSSFWorkbook(100);  // keep 100 rows in memory
       Sheet sh = wb.createSheet();
       for (int rownum = 0; rownum < 1000; rownum++) {
           Row row = sh.createRow(rownum);
           if(rownum == 200)  {
               sh.groupRow(100, 200);
           }

       Workbook wb = new SXSSFWorkbook(100);  // keep 100 rows in memory

      • setRandomAccessWindowSize

        public void setRandomAccessWindowSize(int value)
        Specifies how many rows can be accessed at most via getRow(). When a new node is created via createRow() and the total number of unflushed records would exeed the specified value, then the row with the lowest index value is flushed and cannot be accessed via getRow() anymore. A value of -1 indicates unlimited access. In this case all records that have not been flushed by a call to flush() are available for random access. A value of 0 is not allowed because it would flush any newly created row without having a chance to specify any cells.(指定通过getRow（）最多可以访问多少行。当通过ExpressRow（）创建新节点并且未刷新的记录总数将超出指定值时，则索引值最低的行将被刷新，并且无法再通过getRow（）访问。值为-1表示无限制访问。在这种情况下，所有尚未被调用flush（）刷新的记录都可用于随机访问。不允许使用0值，因为它会刷新任何新创建的行，而没有机会指定任何单元格。)
